subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Anomis mesogona
was revised as
Gonitis mesogona
by Holloway (2005) . Hampson distinguished this species by the excised forewing at the outer margin up to vein M3, where it is produced. There are 2 black spots at end of the forewing’s cell.
